    "body": "You'll want to spawn a new process with the `detached` option set to true, like so:\n\n``` rust\nuse std::io::Command;\nuse std::os;\n\nfn main() {\n    let args = os::args();\n    if args.len() == 1 {\n        let child = Command::new(args.get(0).as_slice())\n                            .arg(\"child\")\n                            .detached().spawn().unwrap();\n        println!(\"child: {}\", child.id());\n        child.forget();\n    } else {\n        println!(\"I'm a daemon!\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is all possible today, so I'm going to close this issue.\n",
